<headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 10 at 3:25AM EDT  by NWS Grand Rapids</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of southern Gratiot,
eastern Ionia, western Clinton and southeastern Montcalm Counties
through 430 AM EDT...
At 325 AM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 7
miles east of Ionia, moving northeast at 25 mph.
HAZARD...Nickel size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.
Locations impacted include...
Ionia...               Portland...            Ithaca...
Grand Ledge...         Lake Odessa...         Carson City...
Sumner...              Fowler...              Sebewa...
North Star...          Westphalia...          Lyons...
Maple Rapids...        Muir...                Mulliken...
Pewamo...              Perrinton...           Hubbardston...
Eagle...               Wacousta...
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.88 IN
MAX WIND GUST...&lt;30 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
